                <h1>Abraham Lincoln: The Iconic Leader Who Freed a Nation</h1>
                <p>Abraham Lincoln, the 16th U.S. president, guided the nation through its Civil War and worked tirelessly to end slavery. Born in 1809, he emphasized equality and unity, delivering the iconic Gettysburg Address. Lincoln's leadership and vision for a united America make him a lasting symbol of democracy and human rights.</p>
